==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: -ol
<hw>-ol</hw> <pr>(-⟦omac⟧l <it>or</it> -⟦ocr⟧l)</pr> <pos>suff.</pos>
<ety>[From alcoh<ets>ol</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A suffix
denoting that the substance in the name of which it appears belongs to
the series of <sig>alcohols</sig> or <sig>hydroxyl derivatives</sig>,
<as>as ethan<ex>ol</ex>, carbin<ex>ol</ex>, phen<ex>ol</ex>,
glycer<ex>ol</ex>, etc.</as> Such compounds contain the hydroxy radical
(<chform>-OH</chform>).</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

